messages.text: I'm in the woods somewhere, I think.
Why are you in the woods?
It's getting dark, and the storm is moving in.
I have no idea where my car is parked.
The last thing I remember is texting Arianna Dossett.
I think I had another seizure.
They can track your phone and take you to the hospital.
Don’t worry about getting locked up anymore.
This is more important—it’s a matter of life and death.
I don't know what else to do.
Call me after you talk to the operator, OK?
He said he would, but then he texted me in Latin again.
I don't know what that means!
Roughly translated, it means "worse things await."
Something like, "The worst is yet to come."
We gotta find a way to break the curse!
I know you don't believe in that stuff, but Ethan needs our help.
We need to focus on finding Ethan and getting him to a hospital.
His mother had a mental illness, and he could be predisposed to one because of that.
But you said Theodore Tate showed signs of a mental illness before Della killed him…
Those are the same symptoms Ethan is experiencing now!
The diary's interesting from a historical perspective, but witchcraft isn’t real.
Look, I'm going to the police station.
I'll give the cops the information they need to track Ethan’s phone.
And I'll let you know if I find anything new, OK?
Why would he leave his phone behind?!
It's dark out. Doesn’t he need the flashlight?
He could've dropped it in the rain.
He told me he could barely walk.
You said you were on the mountain with your family, right?
Yeah. I'm at our cabin by the Falls.
Does Ethan know where the cabin is?
Yes. I threw a graduation party here at the beginning of the summer.
Because Ethan's on the mountain, too.
We found his phone in the woods, about 2 miles from the Falls.
I think he's looking for you.
After the police found Ethan’s phone, I came up here, too.
I need to find my son.
OK. My dad said he'd help look for him, too.
We'll look all around the cabin.
Give us 5 minutes to get dressed and stuff.
I wandered off from my dad.
And he's standing on the edge of the cliff, looking down at the water.
I ran into your dad and we’re on our way to the Falls.
I don't think he even recognizes me.
We’re a few miles away, Brooke.
Focus on getting through to him.
I am. I’m trying my hardest.
